		(uuid "046512dd-b5ec-4938-95e9-72536f9006c6")
	)
	(text_box "The MPPT algorithm is disabled by default at POR (EN_MPPT = 0)\n\nThe algorithm runs automatically when EN_MPPT bit is set to 1.\n\nSimilar to the FORCE_VINDPM_DET feature, when the battery voltage is lower than VSYSMIN (VSYS_STAT\n= 1), the MPPT algorithm can not be enabled. The EN_MPPT bit will be reset back to 0 if it is written to\n1\n\n When VBUS goes below VBUS_PRESENT, the EN_MPPT bit will be reset to 0, and forced\nto be 0 even if the host writes it to 1.\n\nFor the EN_ICO, FORCE_VINDPM_DET and EN_MPPT three register bits, only one of them can be set to 1 at\na given time. If one of them is enabled, the charger will block the host from enabling the other two features until\nthe first is disabled."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 15.24 139.7 0)
		(size 80.01 50.8)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2bb34d95-58f5-4b21-84c9-2e02ca71b433")
	)
